extendedInfo.description: Use your phone or tablet as an offroad topo mapping handheld GPS with the bestselling outdoor navigation app for Android! Explore beyond cell coverage for hiking and trekking.Download topo maps for the US and many other countries in advance, so you won't need cell coverage when navigating. Use GPS waypoints from GPX or KML files, or enter your own coordinates using longitude/latitude, UTM MGRS, or grid reference. Using GOTO makes a waypoint a locus for navigation. This uses many publicly available map sources as free downloads. It also has some additional content available as an in app purchase:-Accuterra Topo Map Source for $19.99/year. This can be purchased and used with or in instead of the free sources.- Boundary maps for 12 western states from the Bureau of Land Management(BLM) for $7.99 each. Overlay for topo maps valued by hunters. -GMU boundaries in some states-Lake Contours in WA,CT,MN-Content from US TrailMaps for $15.99, including:-ATV, Whitewater, and Equestrian Trail Maps, See these in the menu under More-> "Purchasing AddOns". They can be shown on top of topo maps. You may try the DEMO version to make sure you like the maps in your country. About topo (topographic) maps: Topo maps show terrain through color and contours, and are useful for navigation offroad. Topo maps and GPS can be used for hiking, hunting, kayaking, snowshoeing, & backpacker trails. You can create your own maps with Mobile Atlas Creator, or specify a custom tile server. Built in sources include:OpenStreetMaps from MapQuest OpenCycleMaps showing terrain worldwide US Topo Maps from Caltopo and the USGSUSTopo: Aerial Photography with markup. Canada Topo Maps from ToporamaMarine maps: NOAA RNC Nautical Charts (coastal)USGS Color Aerial photography    Topographic Maps of Spain and Italy Topo maps of New Zealand Japan GSI maps.Many of the Above sources are generally free to use. Use offline topo maps and GPS on hiking trails without cell service. The GPS in your Android phone can get its position from GPS satellites, and you donât have to rely on your data plan to get maps. Have more fun and safe GPS adventures in the backcountry.Use for geocaching by getting a pocket query as GPX. Besides geocaching, use GPS for recording tracks and GPS waypoints on your trip, all the while tracking your GPS quest on topographic maps. It may replace your Garmin handheld GPS. Here are some of the outdoor GPS activities BackCountry Navigator has been used for:As a hiking GPS both on hiking trails and off trail.  Camping trips to find that perfect camping site or find your way back to camp with GPS. Hunting trips for hunting wild game in rugged areas. Doing recon for a hunt or a live hunting trip.    Fishing: mark your favorite fishing spots and navigate with GPS. Search and Rescue (SAR). Trekking the Pacific Crest trail or other long term hiking. Kayak and canoe trips on inland lakes and streams or marine, coastal waters.  Backpacker trips: using topo maps of wilderness areas and national forests to navigate on trails with the GPS. Have this in your rucksack or backpack.   Snow adventures including snowmobiling, skiing and snowshoeing.Find your own ways to have fun in the outdoors. Be a maverick by venturing into new territory beyond cell service boundaries with your GPS. Become a pro at navigation with GPS for allsports for the outdoors. BackCountry Navigator has been previously available on WM devices and preloaded on the Trimble Nomad outdoor rugged device. This Android version is more flexible, featured, and fun.For a one time fee, this a great addition to the outdoor gear you bought at Cabelas, REI, or another outdoor store. Many have found the Android GPS in a phone or tablet to substitute for a Garmin GPS or Magellan GPS, such as the Garmin Montana GPS, Garmin Etrex GPS, or the Garmin Oregon GPS. Android can be your handheld GPS.

reviews.comment: Great app. Developer sets the bar for service and maintenance. Could there be an easy way to transfer saved tracks and waypoints to a new phone?

reviews.title: Used all day in the desert. Found it to be very accurate. Great app!
reviews.comment: I\'d buy again. New user learning more each time I use it. Looks more complicated than it really is.
reviews.author: Michael B

reviews.title: Excellent for SAR
reviews.comment: Very helpful for getting search and rescue, helps us plan and record our sorties. well made, great features, and easy to use. Wish aerial photos were higher detail but still great!
reviews.author: Austin Troth

reviews.title: Works well in Canada
reviews.comment: I have been using BackCountry Navigator for several months on a Samsung SGH-T959D. The application is Excellent and Canadian maps are as good as they were on my previous GPS device. Play with BCN for an hour or two and it becomes easy to use. There is some delay in establishing an initial GPS fix on the Samsung that has not totally been solved but I don\'t think that is the fault of BCN as it has been reported by others using other mapping applications. I highly recommend this application.  After another year has gone by I can say that Nathan, the developer, really has the best interests of his users at heart.    BCN is evolving nicely and Nathan maintains contact with purchasers, sending tips and offering explanations why things work the way they do (provided the user subscribes).  I have replaced my Samsung with a Google Nexus 4 and have noticed much better GPS response.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Handy, but...
reviews.comment: Really useful when you\'re out there. But after you think you\'ve downloaded the maps you want, turn off your network connection and test it to make sure!! You may not have gotten the maps you think you did. And deleting unwanted maps takes FOREVER - why? Plus there\'s no way to get an index of your maps - just a list that some maps were downloaded on some date/time.
reviews.author: James Wang

reviews.title: Not ready for serious offline use
reviews.comment: I recently carted my DroidX around the White Clouds of Idaho and Backcountry Navigator kindof sucks.  Problem 1 - No offline help. None. Nadda. Zip. So you better have memorized everything before you head into the backcountry because backcountry navigator pro only has ONLINE help.  Problem 2 - Code design problem. The app uses SQLite, which is fine. Database is in App data space and your maps are on the SD card space. If you clear data on the App because it is acting wonky, you lose the database. The App code doesn\'t know either how to write out the database or rebuild itself. So you are basically hosed. This is a really, really fundamental code boo-boo.  Problem 3 - Code design problem. If you can\'t get a GPS fix after a couple minutes, what should you do? Keep running until the battery dies? Or alert the user? If the software interface to the GPS service is hung, what should you do? Keep wasting battery or alert the user? BCN isn\'t smart enough to alert the user. Instead it simply runs the battery dead. Very, very poor design for offline use.  Is Backcountry navigator worth the hype? Nope. It\'s not ready for serious offline use. And why do I see AdWhirl when I paid $10?
reviews.author: Aunt Belinda

reviews.comment: Threw both my frustrating, expensive GPSs (you know who they are!) in the garbage ...\t\"Colorado Joe\" they call me! I\'m in the mountains every week & weekend. Hiking, snowshoeing, trail-running, Mtn&Road biking (Motorcycling too!). Been using app since ~2009 and I never outdoor without it. Run this on my Note2, it\'s awesome! Download maps, go airplane mode (Make sure GPS enabled) all features needed are available (Too many to list! ... and the great features enhancements keep coming with every update! Nice!). CONS? Mehhh... makes ya wanna get out of the city and out in to the great outdoors! GetIt!
reviews.author: Joe J

reviews.title: Awesome!
reviews.comment: This is the best app ever made! I use it every time I go climb a mountain or hunt for wild mushrooms or do a thru hike. Anything wilderness related. Now and then I check out the dedicated gps devices at rei with their expensive maps and it makes me wonder how they are still in business.  This app and a decent smart phone and anyone is light years ahead of those ridiculous things.  Who buys that stuff?  I don\'t know who you are Mr app maker but my hope is that you are set for life. Brilliant work!
reviews.author: Thaddeus Wells

reviews.comment: Excellent!  Learning curve is a little steep, but is well worth the effort. It could be a tad more intuitive.
reviews.author: Jan Abeita

reviews.title: Great app, helped me find places to hunt!
reviews.comment: My only complaint about this app is when I have the blm overlay (for utah) selected, it takes forever to show boundaries. And when they finally show up if I zoom or even move the map, the overlay disappears. this happens on and offline with saved tiles. If it would just remain on constantly, that would be awesome. Even with that minor flaw, app gets five stars.
reviews.author: Nate Roberson

reviews.title: Best mapping
reviews.comment: I am an avid outdoorsman and retired guide with 35 years of experience in the outdoors. I think that this is the best mapping app that I have. Highly recommend you check it out.
reviews.author: Dale Whitmore

reviews.title: Backcountry success
reviews.comment: Took my Nexus 7 into the Wind River range, Wyoming, for 8 days. Turned on GPS to locate my position on the forest service maps as needed. Waypoints my campsites and measured the 39 miles I hiked. It was most excellent. Great app.
reviews.author: Mark C

reviews.title: Excellent !!!!!
reviews.comment: Best wilderness program period!  Got me out of a jam in a National Forest.
reviews.author: John Smith

reviews.title: Not reliable for downloaded maps offline
reviews.comment: Three times I have downloaded topo and imagry for different areas.  While on the trips it works great for a while but eventually comes up with an error of \"no map source for selected map package\".  Once this occurs there is nothing that can be done to view where I am or to navigate to waypoints.  I suspect there is an underlying database reliability bug that is in the software or a library it uses. I give it 2 stars because it did guide me to find a backcountry lake with no trail, but failed on the return and fortunately I had a paper map and compass.  If the bug was fixed this is a 5 star app.
reviews.author: Kerry Krieske

reviews.title: Life saver
reviews.comment: Worked awesome on my week long hunting trip. Out of he service area. They seem to have worked out all the glitches I was having earlier.
